title: Israel hawks to Trump: Move embassy to Jerusalem QUIETLY | DailyMail.com - Daily Mail
text: show ad Trump edges away from moving Israel embassy to Jerusalem and stakes out middle ground on building new settlements â€“ just as Netanyahu is primed for a visit President says he doesn't want to insult Israel, but building new settlements won't help achieve a lasting Middle East peace He told DailyMail.com last year that Israel should 'keep moving forward' with settlements But in an interview with the Israel Hayom newspaper, he took a far more cautious position Trump is also backing away from Kellyanne Conway's December claim that moving the U.S. embassy in Israel to Jerusalem is a 'very big priority' Now he says he is merely 'studying' the issue Published: 20:26 GMT, 10 February 2017 | Updated: 20:36 GMT, 10 February 2017 11 shares
